    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This fine garment is made of black silk interwoven with faint silvery threads. While wearing it, you gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li><p>You have resistance to poison damage.</p></li><li><p>You have a climbing speed equal to your walking speed.</p></li><li><p>You can move up, down, and across vertical surfaces and upside down along ceilings, while leaving your hands free.</p></li><li><p>You can’t be caught in webs of any sort and can move through webs as if they were difficult terrain.</p></li><li><p>You can use an action to cast the <em>web</em> spell (save DC 13). The web created by the spell fills twice its normal area. Once used, this property of the cloak can’t be used again until the next dawn.</p></li></ul>",
